  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RECLAIM Sustainability! Uganda-Tea</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to:
-Advocate for the development and implementation of policies and regulatory frameworks that enhance sustainable natural resource management in the tea sector.
-Create an inclusive public and business enabling environment that contributes to decent work conditions for small-scale growers, workers with focus on categories of women, youth and other socially marginalised groups in East, Central and Southern Africa tea sector.
-Avocate for transparency in the tea sector that will ensure fair value distribution along the nodes of the value chain for the benefit of all actors. Especially the actors, including the invisible women at the production node of the value chain towards improved livelihoods and access to available safe dietary diverse nutritious food.
-Create innovative digital tools and new business models that will ensure farmers and workers have access to fair data and ownership of more tea business processes.
-Strengthen workers and farmer groups and create networks to enhance access to knowledge and information, facilitate an informed dialogue in which women, youth and other marginalized groups can speak up, and policy makers can make informed decisions by 2025.</narrative>
  </description>
